Method Detail

getDisplayFont

public Font getDisplayFont()
Deprecated. 
Description copied from interface: LayerInfo
Obtains a font that can be used to display the layer name and other details such as Renderer (for FeatureLayer) in a user interface, such as Legend or Catalog. Usually this font is obtained from an ArcIMS service, and is to assist multi-lingual capabilities of the ArcIMS client. If the client does not actually have the required font, it is expected that a default font will be used, and that a warning message will already have been sent to the MessageCentre - calling code need not detect the presence or absence of this font.

Specified by:
getDisplayFont in interface LayerInfo
Returns:
the display font
See Also:
LayerInfo.setDisplayFont(java.awt.Font)
